I remember 31 December 1967.  The day OR nurses were sitting around in our hooch talking about New Year's Eve back in the World and what 1968 would bring.  We wondered when the first guy would die in our hospital in 1968.  We wondered who he would be.  It was a sinister twist on the idle habit people have of taking bets on the delivery date of a baby.  We soon had our answer.  <br><br>
I wish we had never had that frivolous conversation.  When the new year arrives, I cannot make resolutions.  I cannot drink champagne.  I remember too much.<br><br>
Dusty    USANC   RVN 66-67, 67-68
